%N A158344 Number of n-colorings of the Folkman Graph.
%C A158344 The Folkman Graph has 20 vertices and 40 edges. It is the semi-symmetric graph with the fewest possible vertices.
%H A158344 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A158344/b158344.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A158344 Jon Folkman, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0021-9800(67)80069-3">Regular line-symmetric graphs</a>, Journal of Combinatorial Theory, 3 (3) (1967), 215-232.
%H A158344 Marc Timme, Frank van Bussel, Denny Fliegner, and Sebastian Stolzenberg, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1088/1367-2630/11/2/023001">Counting complex disordered states by efficient pattern matching: chromatic polynomials and Potts partition functions</a>, New J. Phys. 11 023001 (2009).
%H A158344 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/FolkmanGraph.html">Folkman Graph</a>.
